Description: Ring foot and base sherd of Egyptian black ware pottery open vessel, possibly a plate; simple ring foot; floor offset from rim on inside; dark red to dull brown Nile silt fabric with mica inclusions; worn dull black slip on interior and exterior save for underside; inscription on underside.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (IC.086)
